    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the art and architecture that coincided with the rule of Mahmud I, who ruled from 1730 to 1754.  He built several fountains during his reign including the large Indian-inspired fountain of Tophane. Also under his supervision was the Nuruosmaniye mosque, which broke from Ottoman tradition with more Western style rectangular ground plans.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026081/Levey, World of Ottoman Art (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de kunst en architectuur in de periode van de heerschappij van Mahmoed I, die regeerde van 1730 tot 1754. Tijdens zijn heerschappij bouwde hij verschillende fonteinen, waaronder de grote op India geïnspireerde fontein van Tophane. Onder zijn supervisie viel ook de Nuruosmaniye-moskee, die brak met de Ottomaanse traditie en die was gebouwd op basis van rechthoekige grondplannen in een meer westerse stijl.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用來表示西元 1730 年至 1754 年間，與馬哈穆德一世統治時期有關的藝術與建築。馬哈穆德一世在位期間建造了數座噴泉，包括一座受到印度文化啟發的大型噴泉「炮門噴泉」（Fountain of Tophane）。此外，奴魯歐斯曼清真寺（Nuruosmaniye Mosque）在他的監督下建造；這座清真寺打破了鄂圖曼的傳統，採用更加西化風格的矩形平面配置。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
